parameters:
\n<Female>Throwing trash down below is an act of charity. It's
certainly not a bad thing. It's about giving what's needed
to those who need it.

\n<Female>I never wear the same clothes twice. That's why I often
throw them away, but I'm sure the people living below must
be happy to receive them.

\n<Man>Don't come any closer, it's dangerous. We throw trash down
from here. If you lean out too much, you might fall
yourself.

\n<Man>If you fall from here and by some miracle survive, you'll be
stripped bare to the skin. They're like demons, peeling
everything off, even if you're injured.

\n<Man>I really don't need this bed anymore. If I drop it down, it
could at least serve as firewood. I'm someone who can
consider the people living below, after all.

\n<Man>This area ahead is a garbage dump. Be careful when you throw
things down there. Are you the type to care?

\n<Man>Ah, sorry. I mean, would you care if something you threw hit
someone and they died?
Of course!
Not really...

\n<Man>Right. There are people like that sometimes. The type who
throw things without checking below. Imagine if it hit
someone. You'd be the type to lose sleep over it, wouldn't
you?

\n<Man>You know, what do you think of the residents of Dri-Ne? Oh,
are you the type who can easily cut down a monster that
looks like a person? I see. So you're the type with no
qualms about that. An unpleasant type.

\n<Adventurer A>Oh, it's you from that time! How are you? Are you here for
work today?

\n<Adventurer A>The security job for that thief last time was easy, huh?
After all, we just stood around, and we got paid as usual.

\n<Adventurer A>After that, the captain of the guards got a real earful.
That's definitely going to be a demotion.
\n<Adventurer A>Hey, \n[1]... that was your name, right? How's it going?

\n<Adventurer A>Ever since then, the Count Noblesse has been acting strange.
It seems like he's preparing for something big. A lot of
large carriages have been passing through.

\n<Adventurer A>Well, it's none of my business really. I'm an adventurer,
after all. Non-interference in domestic affairs outside of
work is my principle. I just want to live freely, you know.

This is the entrance to the Rumare Guild. It doesn't smell
as much of alcohol compared to downstairs... I should have
registered here.

It looks like a fancy inn... I'm sure the futons and beds
are soft and warm. The receptionist must be more pleasant
than that old lady too.

This is probably the inn where grandpa is staying. Hmm, it's
kind of making me angry.

Training log. This is a very sturdy wood. Even if you slash
it with a sword, it only gets slightly scratched.

I bet the people in the upper guild are training properly.
As for everyone below... I hardly see them doing anything
other than drinking.

A training log. This is a very sturdy piece of wood. It's
been reinforced with a barrier spell, so it seems like it
would feel great to cast magic on it.

Since the guard station is nearby, it seems the town guards
are properly trained. The guard below... was there a guard
below?

It's a statue of a goddess. I wonder who the model was. It's
incredibly beautiful.

It's a statue of a goddess. I wonder who the model was. It's
incredibly beautiful.

Cool armor, but the size is too big. I wonder if I'll be
able to wear it eventually.

Quality material for clothes. They seem comfortable to wear,
durable, and while simple, these are definitely worth
buying. If only there was a hole for the tail...

It's a robe for magicians. It's not like magicians can't
wear armor, but somehow a robe just feels more fitting.

Clothes that are both cute and practical. Perfect for an
adventure! I'll buy them next time.

The symbol of the noble district "Ruma-Re," the Water Dragon
Fountain. It is said that if you make a wish and throw a
coin into the fountain, the probability of your wish coming
true increases with the amount of money you throw in.
Hmm... how mercenary.

The clothing and accessories store "Vetumo" guarantees
you'll find the perfect outfit. We also have armor, so
travelers are welcome too!
Huh...? What a strange name.

It's bread that feels like it was just baked! It's been a
while since I've seen one! Smells good... Yes, this is what
bread was supposed to be.

The bread in Dori-ne is as hard as a rock! Bread that could
kill you if you hit your head with it isn't really bread at
all...

It's an apple. If it's allowed, I want to take a bite. Even
if I get scolded, I still want to bite into it.
\n<\n[1]>T-taru!

A lodging with beds so comfortable you look forward to
sleeping, and a delicious breakfast that makes waking up a
delight! Please inquire at the reception when you stay

\n<\n[1]>...(A bed you can't sleep in, and a breakfast so awful it's
made by an old lady. It's a far cry from the inn below.)
\n<\n[1]>T-tar!

The jar is filled with water. The medaka fish are swimming
around, looking so cool...
\n<\n[1]>T-tar!

Some kind of trash. I guess this goes down below too. It
stinks and seems like no one would want it.

It's a slightly worn-out bed. It seems better than the dirty
one below. I wish I could take it home...

A log is placed here. It's riddled with holes where bugs
have eaten through it.

Is it a birthday? Even if it is, that's quite an extravagant
cake. I want to eat it.

It's an assortment of fruits. Fruits from different seasons
are mixed together on the plate. It seems they're harvested
with temperature control using freezing and scorching
techniques.
But more importantly, I want to eat it.

I never thought I'd be this envious of fried eggs and
bread... But for now, I must resist. I'll keep at it until
everything is finished. But I want to eat it.

It's a lunch set. Eating outside so elegantly must be the
best time. I'm jealous... I want to eat it.

Drinking from the afternoon is the same for those above as
it is for those below.

The aroma of the black tea is delightful. I'd be content
just smelling it, but if possible, I'd love to have a taste.

\n<Female>...(Sigh... Such a boring, pretentious man. I want to go
home already.)
\n<Rabbit Beastman>Ah! Hello! Nfufu- It's so nice to meet a fellow beastman

\n<Rabbit Beastman>We're treated the same as humans, but being a beastman still
makes us stand out a bit, doesn't it? Are you free after
this? Let's go grab some food

\n<\n[1]>Ah, sorry! I have to work, so maybe another time
(Rabbits... I'm not good with them...)

\n<\n[1]>Ah, um, well... I, I have work! So let's do it another time!
(I don't have good memories with rabbit beastmen...)

\n<Rabbit Beastman>Work? You're kidding, right I can tell these things Come
on- come on Let's kill some time together? Come on- come
on- come on

\n<\n[1]>Ah-! Don't pull my arm! It's broken there! Ouch ouch ouch!
See you later! Bye-bye! (So persistent! Are they all like
this?!)

\n<\n[1]>No, really, I have work! Hey, don't pull on my arm! Guard!
Guard!! (Rabbits are really forceful, huh!)

\n<Rabbit Beastman>Hmph. So that's how you're going to be. Uuu... I'm sad...
Feh... Fehhhhhhhn! Just kidding-pyon Ahahahaha
\n<\n[1]>...(What a hassle... Better not to get involved. So tiring.)
\n<\n[1]>...(Ugh. Annoying.)

Drinking from the afternoon is the same for those above as
it is for those below.

The aroma of the black tea is delightful. I'd be content
just smelling it, but if possible, I'd love to have a taste.

The scent of the black tea is lovely. I'd be content with
just the smell, but I'd love to have a taste if possible.

It seems like they're selling equipment. Should I buy
something?

It's a Flame Tree stove. By setting the sap of the Flame
Tree below and igniting it, it burns for a long timea truly
excellent item.

The Flame Tree is a conifer that burns its own leaves before
winter, becoming completely bare. It often causes forest
fires.
It seems like they're in the middle of cooking something.

It seems like you wouldn't get food poisoning from cooking
outside in a town with such clean water.

This is the guard station of Rumare. It's divided into the
extermination team, which ensures that monsters don't
approach the town walls, and the security team, which
maintains order within the town.

Incidentally, one of the adventurer's jobs is to go further
than the extermination team to defeat monsters.

\n<Female>I heard the hero carries a big sword and travels with a
dragon as a pet! They must be an incredibly imposing man!

\n<Female>If you see someone with a big sword and a dragon, that's the
mark of the hero. It's easy to recognize, but it's a bit
intimidating to approach, isn't it? Scary!

\n<Female>Lately, it seems that the number of humanoid monsters has
been increasing. There have always been such creatures, but
the ones now look much closer to humans.

\n<Female>They have distinguishing features like horns, wings, or
tails, but those are also characteristics of you
beastfolk... Eventually, it might become difficult to tell
beastfolk and monsters apart...

\n<Female>Oh, I'm sorry! Please don't misunderstand me? I just don't
want it to become like the old days where beastfolk were
discriminated against. That's something I'm a bit worried
about.

\n<Student>You know, have you heard about that rumor? There's this boy
who went missing, you know. That, what's his name... I
forgot, but he's a plain-looking guy.

\n<Student>They say he was with the student council president right up
until he disappeared. Maybe she's the culprit? For real.

\n<Student>Just between us, you know Arno, right? The student council
president. I heard they might actually be a monster.

\n<Student>No, really! Remember the day we couldn't use the classroom
because of the barrier spell? Arno has been missing since
then. It's gotta be true.

\n<Student>They were always so serious, but to be honest, I was kind of
scared of them.

\n<Student>The student council president isn't such a bad kid. Unlike a
delinquent like you, they're serious about their duties.

\n<Student>What do you mean by 'the culprit of the disappearance'? Are
you suggesting they killed someone and buried the body?
That's a seriously scary thought. It's more believable that
you bullied them into not coming to school.

\n<Student>So, like, Arno-chan isn't a monster, you know. It's because
of weird rumors spread by people like you that she's been
out for so long. Poor thing.

\n<Student>And about that barrier spell incident in the classroom,
there was an explanation that dangerous gas was released
because chemicals got mixed up, right? You really love those
kinds of rumors. Like conspiracy theories and stuff.

\n<Stall>Hm? Are you two twins? Oh my, you look so alike How cute
Seeing you both side by side makes you twice as adorable
I'll give you a little service

\n<\n[1]>For all that talk, it's pretty expensive. Give us more of a
service.

\n<Stall>Oh, what a cute customer If there's anything you'd like to
eat, just let me know If you let me touch your ear, I'll
give you a little extra
\n<\n[1]>You're giving a bonus at this price?

\n<Magician>Greetings. Are you also staying at this inn? I stopped by on
my journey, and this has been the most splendid lodging I've
found.

\n<Magician>There's even a little hot spring in the back. It's not
natural, but a healing mage has dissolved magical power into
it, so it leaves your skin glowing

\n<Magician>The cuisine was also marvelous, with a focus on quality
ingredients. The bed was like sleeping on a cloud, they even
managed to give it a sense of floating.

\n<\n[1]>...(This person isn't bad at all. Yet, I'm getting the urge
to scratch them.)

\n<Man>It's so peaceful, isn't it? Such calm weather. What do you
think? This town is a really beautiful place, right?

\n<Man>But you know, just beyond the gate you can see from here,
there's a huge hole that opened up about 50 years ago due to
land subsidence.

\n<Man>It was a phenomenon called a sinkhole. One day, the ground
suddenly collapsed, and the hole opened up. Many homes and
people were caught up in it and sank down.

\n<Man>Those people probably were saying things like "It's peaceful
today. The weather is nice," right up until the moment it
happened.

\n<Man>My father died in the great collapse 50 years ago. But
that's okay. It was a natural disaster. Sad as it was, I had
to accept it.

\n<Man>But what I can't forgive are those who came after. Hearing
that the nobles' district had collapsed, scoundrels from all
over the world gathered, lured by the prospect of gold and
goods.

\n<Man>They prioritized collecting precious metals over rescuing
people buried under the rubble.

\n<Man>As a child, I watched from the cliffs every day. They were
scrambling over each other, sometimes fighting, all over the
debris where my home once stood.

\n<Man>Now it's called "Dri-Ne" and has become a different
autonomous district... But I still don't acknowledge those
people, not even now.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper A>Are you one of the adventurers from below? You may pass.
Adventurers are treated as "those who belong nowhere."
Basically, if there's a request, you can enter anywhere.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper A>But that also means "you always have no allies." If there's
any inconvenience, we, the guards of Lumare, will thoroughly
eliminate you. Understood?

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>A few years back, there was a bit of a riot. My best friend
was stabbed to death by one of those Driane guys. He was a
really good person.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>He had a beautiful wife and even a little kid... Just when
his life was about to start, everything was taken from him.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>We, the guards of Lumare, have to keep watch over both
monsters and humans to ensure that such a tragedy never
happens again.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>A few years ago, there was a bit of a riot. My best friend
was stabbed to death by a Drine. He was a really good guy.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>He had a beautiful wife and even a little kid... Just when
his life was about to start, everything was taken from him.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>We, the guards of Lumare, have to keep watch over both
monsters and humans to ensure such tragedies never happen
again...

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>And yet, just recently, that guy's wife was killed by a
monster too. His son has been left all alone.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>The kid's name is Jean. He's been taken in by the Lumare
orphanage now.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>I go to see him too, and he's really a strong kid. He says
he wants to become an adventurer specializing in monster
extermination, to reduce the sorrow in this world even a
little bit.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>I can only protect, but you can save people. Please continue
to save many more. I'll do my best to protect this town too.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>You might be busy, but please show your face to Jean and
Mare-san once in a while. Jean is a big fan of yours, after
all.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>A few years ago, there was a bit of a riot. My best friend
was stabbed by a Drine and died. He was truly a good person.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>He had a beautiful wife and even a small child... Just when
his life was about to start, everything was taken from him.
\n<\n[1]>Are you talking about Mare-san and Jean?

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>Oh! So you knew them? What a coincidence! Yes, they are my
best friend's family. Huh? Could it be that you're the one
who...

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>Thank you for saving them. My best friend must be thanking
you from heaven too. Here, would you accept this?

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>This is something Mare-san's husband, my best friend, gave
to me. It's equipment that will increase your fighting
power. I want you to have it.

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>I can only protect, but you can save people. Please continue
to save many more. I'll do my best to protect this town too.

\n<Soldier>Hmph! Ha! Tuh!! Whoa there, you're in the middle of training
right now! If you get too close, you might get hurt!

\n<Adventurer C>"The phantom thief was too fast... I couldn't do anything.
Maybe I need to train to increase my casting speed.
Sacrifice firepower for burst speed..."

\n<Adventurer C>"No, that won't do. I've always been bad at physical
activities. I can only take my time to charge up and
release."

\n<Adventurer C>"It seems the Noblesse Earl is gathering magicians. I wonder
what he's planning this time. I've been invited too, but
something smells fishy, so I'll pass."

\n<Adventurer C>"I'm planning to leave this town soon. It's pretty here, but
I prefer towns with the smell of oil and such. Maybe I'll
head to Emberland."

\n<Soldier>No abnormalities! The town remains unchanged today as well!
All is well, all is well!

\n<Soldier>You can throw away trash, but make sure to drop it from the
designated place, okay? There are residents below. There are
idiots who throw things over the barrier just because
they're small.

\n<Beautiful Woman>Oh, hello there. It's quite rare to see a cat beastperson
around here. Did you come from far away?

\n<Beautiful Woman>Just a while ago, someone who looks a lot like you passed
by. Are they your sibling?

\n<Beautiful Woman>Now that I think about it, the Catfield family's son and
daughter are indeed twins, if I recall correctly. Could it
be that...

\n<\n[1]>No, that's not it! They say there are at least three people
in the world who look like you! That's it!

\n<Beautiful Woman>Oh my! To think I'd see two out of three on such a day.
Today must be special indeed. Have a wonderful day yourself!

\n<Beautiful Woman>Oh my, could you possibly be from the Catfield family? I am
in your debt. I never expected to meet you in such a place.

\n<\n[1]>N-No, that's not it! I'm not from a fine family like the
Catfields!

\n<Beautiful Woman>Oh, is that so? But there's a "CF" embroidered on your
chest...

\n<\n[1]>I'm just an admirer. It's fake! Ehehe After all, it's a
prestigious family, isn't it? Any beastperson cat would
dream of it.

\n<\n[1]>Ah, this was something I received from someone of the
Catfield family a while ago. It was so honorable that I've
kept it on me at all times.

\n<Beautiful Woman>I see. I must have misunderstood. You seemed so wise, I just
assumed you were from that lineage. My apologies.
\n<\n[1]>... (Did I manage to get through that...)

\n<Beautiful Woman>By the way... I heard that the young master and young lady
of the Catfield family have recently run away from home or
something...

\n<\n[1]>That's terrible! If I see them, I'll make sure to report it!
(I need to get out of here quickly...)

\n<Man>It seems that the Noblesse Count has received another
advance notice. His place is often targeted, must be tough.
My house has only been robbed three times in comparison.
Hahaha!

\n<Man>The trick to not having your valuables stolen is to
deliberately leave something fairly expensive in plain
sight. That way, they get satisfied and leave quickly.

\n<Man>You must never show off your truly precious treasures. They
should be special items known only to yourself and your
family.

\n<Man>It seems the Noblesse Earl has announced possession of the
Call of the Wolf Stone. Really, what is he thinking? Doing
such a thing will surely make him a target for "L".

\n<Man>That's one of the world's leading yellow diamonds. I've only
seen it in an illustrated book myself. Honestly, it's
dubious whether he truly has it or not.

\n<Man>It seems the Noblesse Earl's Call of the Wolf Stone has been
stolen. Despite my warnings not to make it public... Such a
gem is beyond the level of what an individual should
possess.

\n<Man>If it falls into the hands of someone who doesn't understand
its value, they might break it apart to sell it off in
pieces. That would be a loss for the whole world.

\n<Man>It seems the phantom thief has been caught, but the
whereabouts of the Howling Stone remain unknown. We should
interrogate them, and if they crack... Such a gem shouldn't
be owned by an individual.

\n<Man>If it falls into the hands of someone who doesn't understand
its value, they might break it apart to sell it off in
pieces. That would be a loss for the whole world.

\n<Man>Well, at least now I don't have to worry about it being
stolen from our house. But what on earth is Count Noblesse
thinking? I can't comprehend his thoughts at all.

\n<Female>*burp* Ahh~ Daytime beer is the best Watching the soldiers
work while I drink makes it even better... you know It just
goes down smoother with a bit of guilt~

\n<Female>You really don't need to be on edge guarding every day.
Riots hardly ever happen! And monsters don't come into town
either

\n<Female>Let's see, today I'm stopping by the boutique, then getting
my hair done. After that, it's tea time with friends, and
then dinner with him. Ah, I'm so busy! I have absolutely no
free time!

\n<\n[1]>...(It looks like they have nothing but free time... But I
guess everyone has different things they must do.)

\n<Female>And tomorrow, I have to go to the dog salon in the morning,
then it's a girls' lunch, right? After that, I'm off to see
a play with a different guy... Ahh! Seriously! Why am I so
busy!

\n<\n[1]>(No, on second thought, this person really does seem to have
a lot of free time.)

\n<Female>My partner is usually kind, but when they drink, they just
keep complaining about the people from Dri-Ne. I can
understand the feeling, though.

\n<Female>Since I don't know the horrors of the collapse, I think it
would be nice if everyone could get along without any
hierarchy. But that's just wishful thinking.

\n<Female>Even if they don't say it out loud, there are many who
resent the people from Dri-Ne. Everyone looks down on them
in some part of their heart.

\n<Female>More than the people of Dri-Ne, I'm worried that the
dissatisfaction of the people in this town might explode
someday.

\n<Man>Oh my, are you an adventurer? I'm sorry, but I'm in the
middle of an important tea time. Could you please not come
any closer?

\n<Man>You might not realize it, but you're steeped in the scent of
monster blood. It ruins the aroma of my tea.

\n<\n[1]>Sniff sniff...? I don't smell anything? My sense of smell is
many times better than an average person's. It must be your
imagination.

\n<\n[1]>Sniff sniff...? Really? I can't smell anything at all. And I
have a much better nose than humans. Strange.

\n<Man>It's a matter of spirituality. Adventurers with their bloody
lifestyle are simply incompatible with me. If you had any
common sense, no explanation would be necessary, would it?

\n<\n[1]>Sorry I don't get it! But I can tell you're a nasty person!
I feel sorry for the tea that gets drunk by you! Bye then!

\n<\n[1]>(I secretly mixed some crushed coins into the tea with a
sleight of hand. Drink up and get diarrhea! Idiot!)

\n<\n[1]>Ah, please enjoy your tea. (So there are people who harbor
such feelings towards adventurers. Better to avoid further
involvement.)

\n<\n[1]>(I also secretly added some sand to the tea with a sleight
of hand. Enjoy your gravel tea.)

\n<Muscular Woman>Ahh, it's so heavy. I can't walk to the trash dump anymore!
This trash must weigh around 180kg! I'm gonna get all
muscly!

\n<Maid>Master~? Where have you gone~? Master~? It's time for the
meeting~!

\n<Soldier>The north side of the slum district "Dori-ne" was heavily
collapsed. It's almost a vertical cliff, isn't it?

\n<Soldier>But the south side was a bit better. That's why remnants of
when it was a noble district still remain, and instead of a
cliff, it's more like a steep slope.

\n<Soldier>The residents who flow into the slums mostly come from the
south. Maybe there's something that draws them in, something
like a fateful current.

\n<Soldier>This is the noble district "Luma-Le". A town with beautiful
water. The specialty here is Luma-Le Chocolates. They're a
bit pricey, but so delicious they'll make you grin from ear
to ear.

\n<Heavily-Armored Adventurer>Rumors of a cat beastman adventurer...? Ah, I know of them.
They're twins, right?

\n<Heavily-Armored Adventurer>Oh, that's you? Anyone else? Hmm... sorry, I can't think of
anyone.

\n<Heavily-Armored Adventurer>Rumors of a cat beastkin adventurer...? Ah, I know of them.
They're the one traveling with the hero, right?

\n<Heavily-Armored Adventurer>Despite fighting barehanded, they're said to be incredibly
strong. They were in the royal capital of Anis not too long
ago, but who knows where they are now. Being an adventurer
and all, they might have moved to a different base.

\n<\n[1]>An adventure with the hero...? My sister...? Hmm, could that
really be true?

\n<\n[1]>Fighting barehanded is just like my sister... But a hero?
Part of such an amazing person's group? I doubt it...

\n<Longsword Adventurer>A strong cat beast-person...? Hmm, I do have someone in
mind, but they're not an adventurer.

\n<Longsword Adventurer>There were rumors about a cat beast-person causing a ruckus
around the Oregano area. They were so out of control that a
subjugation request was even issued.

\n<Longsword Adventurer>They were shouting "Come out, strong ones!" while snapping
trees and beating up adventurers, causing quite the
commotion. I don't know if that situation was ever resolved.

\n<\n[1]>A subjugation request, huh? Hmm, that doesn't sound like my
sister. Thanks!

\n<\n[1]>Ah, that must be someone else then. Thank you very much.
(Please, let it be someone else!)
\n<Longsword Adventurer>I hope you find your sister.

\n<Wanz>Oh, \n[1]! I found a cute dress! I want to buy this after
working hard- How much is it-?

\n<Wanz>Hmm, let's see, zero and one, two-, three, four-, five-,
six... It's 1,000,000G?! Huh?

\n<Wanz>You can't just leave something like that outside! What about
the wind, or rain, or sand?!
\n<Wanz>I hate this outfit. I don't need it.
\n<\n[1]>Louie! Why are you looking at dresses?

\n<Louie>Ah, \n[1]. No reason, just thought they looked cute. I
think you'd look good in one too.
\n<\n[1]>Is that a compliment?

\n<Louie>Eh? Did it not sound like one? Sorry. I genuinely thought it
would suit you.
\n<\n[1]>Just "genuinely"?

\n<Louie>I think it would suit you the best in the world. (Girls can
be so troublesome.)
\n<\n[1]>Then buy it for me
\n<Louie>No way.
It's a very cute dress. Any girl would want to wear it.
\n<Wanz>Munch munch munch munch... Ah...

\n<Wanz>You know, there are times when you just have to eat
something sweet. It's not a waste of money or anything.

\n<Wanz>Please keep it a secret from the guild members, okay? If
they find out I was eating strawberry mille-feuille in the
noble district, they'll think I'm a traitor.

\n<Wanz>It seems like nobody really likes those higher-ups. Only
Latier has a pass to go through, after all. They should get
along better. It's delicious, after all.
\n<\n[1]>Louie! What are you eating?

\n<Louie>\n[1]! Mmph! Cough! Don't just start talking to me out of
nowhere! Cough! It went down the wrong way! Cough cough!
